Etymology[edit]

ex- + hūmor.

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ek.suːˈmoː.roː/, [ɛk.s̠uːˈmoː.ɾoː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ek.suˈmo.ro/, [ɛk.suˈmɔː.rɔ]

Verb[edit]

exhūmōrō (present infinitive exhūmōrāre, perfect active exhūmōrāvī, supine exhūmōrātum); first conjugation

  1. I free from (injurious) humors.
